stylometry: @RISK is a model that allows you to run several simulations at once. If you run a simulation with 5 inputs, this means you are running 5 different simulations, with 1,000 iterations, at one time. Once the simulations are run, this gives you 5 different solutions. You can analyze the data by looking at each of the 5 simulations' averages, minimum, and maximum, standard deviation, etc. @RISK allows you to view these 5 simulations at once and compare its distributions. Even though one simulation may result in the highest average, this does not mean it is the best solution. This simulation may also have the highest standard deviation, which means you cannot put a lot of faith in the data. So it is important to compare all of the factors from all of the 5 simulations before making a decision.
